Package: pilot-link
Version: 0.11.5
Revision: 1
###
GCC: 3.1
###
Depends: libpng-shlibs | libpng3-shlibs, readline-shlibs, tcltk-shlibs, python | python-nox, %N-bin (= %v-%r), %N-shlibs (= %v-%r)
BuildDepends: fink (>= 0.9.9), libpng | libpng3, readline, tcltk, tcltk-dev
BuildDependsOnly: true
###
Source: http://pilot-link.org/source/%n-%v.tar.bz2
Source-MD5: f7e9d73959d9e1d998837e93d03c58e7
###
Patch: %f.patch
NoSetLDFLAGS: true
###
ConfigureParams: --with-perl=/usr/bin/perl --with-pic --with-readline --enable-shared --enable-static --with-tcl=%p --without-itcl --with-tk=%p --with-java=/Library/Java/Home --with-python --with-libiconv --with-libpng --disable-debug --mandir=%i/share/man --infodir=%p/share/info --libexecdir=%p/lib
###
DocFiles: COPYING*
###
Splitoff: <<
  Package: %N-shlibs
  Suggests: %N-bin
  Files: <<
    lib/libpisock.*.dylib 
    lib/libpisock++.*.dylib
    lib/libisync.*.dylib
  <<
  Shlibs: <<
    %p/lib/libpisock.8.dylib %N (>= %v-%r)
    %p/lib/libpisock++.0.dylib %N (>= %v-%r)
    %p/lib/libisync.0.dylib %N (>= %v-%r)
  <<
  DocFiles: AUTHORS COPYING* ChangeLog INSTALL NEWS README
<<
Splitoff2: <<
  Package: %N-bin
  Depends: %N-shlibs (= %v-%r)
  Files: <<
    bin
    share/man
    share/pilot-link
  <<
  DocFiles: COPYING*
<<
###
Description: Palm libraries                             
DescDetail: <<
Pilot-Link is the tools and toys needed to connect your Palm or Palm
compatible handheld (including Handspring, Sony, and Palm) with Unix
and Linux machines.
<<
DescPort: <<
Had to disable tcl/tk support till the maintainer of either x11 or tcltk
fixes a header file.
<<
